text:
Jessica Alba has given birth to a baby boy.
The Hollywood star, 36, and her husband Cash Warren welcomed their new arrival on December 31 - and said it was the perfect way to see in 2018.
Jessica Alba welcomed a baby boy named Hayes on New Year's Eve
Alba shared a picture of newborn Hayes on Instagram and wrote: "Hayes Alba Warren 12/31/17.
"Best gift to ring in the New Year!!
"Cash and I feel so blessed."
Jessica and Cash are already parents to daughters Honor, nine, and Haven, six.
AP:Associated Press Jessica Alba and Cash Warren were thrilled to announce the latest addition to their family
Getty - Contributor Cash and Jessica are proud parents to daughters Honor and Haven
The actress said they "are already obsessed with their new baby bro".
She added the hashtag "#familyof5".
Jessica revealed the sex of her baby back in October, posting a a snap on Instagram with the happy news.
Jessica said: “@cash_warren and I couldn’t be more thrilled to announce...
“#officiallyoutnumbered #babyboy #cantwaittospoilhim #hugsandkissesforlife #soontobemamaofthree!”

Jessica revealed she was expecting her third baby with Cash in an adorable Instagram video in July.
Speaking to The Sun's Fabulous magazine last year, the businesswoman and film star praised her “incredible” life as a mum.
She told us: “I was a lot more critical of my body [before having kids] when it was probably pretty awesome. I was so skinny!
“I was much more stressed and concerned about my body before I had kids.
“But now I know how silly and unimportant it is, so it’s certainly given me perspective.”
title: Jessica Alba gives birth to a baby boy and his name matches daughters Haven and Honor
